4. Staff Dashboard & Data Input
A custom dashboard is the primary "Source of Truth." It is segmented by roles: 
Pharmacy: Tracks drug procurement and sales data automatically.
Clinical: Nurses and doctors input ward updates, vitals, and surgical prep status.
Admin: Manages shift rosters to ensure the AI knows which senior staff are on duty.
"The system must utilize strict schema validation (Zod) to ensure that every entry—from
drug dosages to surgery times—is accurate and formatted correctly for the AI to
interpret." 
5. Security & Privacy Roadmap
Due to the sensitive nature of hospital and industrial data, the infrastructure follows a Private-First
protocol: 
Local Hosting: The LLM is hosted on local hardware (GPUs like NVIDIA RTX 4090) to ensure no
data leaves the building.
Audit Trails: Every AI-generated response includes a timestamp and references the specific
dashboard entry it used.
Encryption: AES-256 encryption for all patient-identifiable information at rest.
6. Implementation Phases
Phase 1: Setup private server environment and core PostgreSQL schema.
Phase 2: Build custom dashboards for data ingestion across departments.
Phase 3: Deploy the local LLM and integrate the RAG orchestration (LangChain).
Phase 4: Testing, safety guardrails, and accuracy fine-tuning.
